Place yolks, SPLENDA(R) Granulated Sweetener, lemon, lavender and 1/4 cup heavy cream in a small mixing bowl. Whisk until smooth. Heat water in the bottom half of a double boiler over medium high heat until simmering. Pour sauce into the top of a double boiler and place over the simmering water. Cook 50-60 seconds, whisking constantly, until the mixture begins to thicken and reaches 170 degrees F. Remove from heat immediately. Pour mixture into a large mixing bowl. Set aside. Pour remaining cream and the creme fraiche into a medium mixing bowl. Whisk together until blended. Slowly stir cream mixture into egg yolk mixture. Stir, using a whisk, until blended. Pour Sabayon through a fine strainer to remove lavender flowers. Place melon into eight serving dishes. Pour sabayon over melon and serve immediately.